{
  "texts": [
    "2.8 When it comes to the impact of recommender systems on opinion dynamics, research is even more at an emerging stage, with for example, only eight papers in the WoS matching the query \"opinion dynamics\" AND (\"recommender systems\" OR \"content recommendation\" OR recommenders), the oldest paper dating from 2015.",
    "Expression associated to this research are both on the periphery of the research landscape (Figure 1) and emerging in the phylomemy (Figure 2).",
    "Before reviewing this tiny literature, it is worth mapping the entire literature on recommendation systems applied to social media in order to better qualify its interactions with the literature on opinion dynamics.",
    "Recommender systems and social media litterature 2.10 The query (\"recommender systems\" OR \"content recommendation\") AND (Twitter OR Facebook OR \"social network\" OR \"online social media\") in the WoS identifies 1,267 papers, the oldest of which dates back to 2004, the year Facebook was founded.",
    "We can clearly see on the mapping of this literature (Figure 3) that it is mainly focused on a user-centric approach of recommender systems with the goal of either mitigating information overload, optimizing information retrieval or maximizing sales."
  ]
}